# Research Chat SDK Fit/Gap

## Step

The contract-v2 decision and the provisioning step both wait on facts
about [vercel/chat](https://github.com/vercel/chat). Resolved when a
linked asset answers, with receipts (docs/source links, not vibes):

- **Adapter reality** for Discord, Telegram, Slack: DM support (not
  just channels), proactive/bot-initiated sends (our whole outbound is
  unprompted), reaction events in, threads, cards/buttons, streaming;
  per-adapter feature gaps.
- **Inbound reality** (full replatform is the finish line): message
  and mention events, slash commands, button/modal interactions,
  self-originated-message filtering (the self-wake-loop defense),
  concurrency controls (burst/queue/debounce) — enough to judge
  whether the Discord-driven dispatcher and operator relay can ride
  the SDK without semantic loss.
- **Hosting model**: what the bot process is (long-running node?
  serverless-first? Next.js-coupled?), what it needs to run on flagg
  under a LaunchAgent, webhook vs socket per platform.
- **Auth/provisioning**: exactly what tokens/apps each of the three
  platforms needs, and whether existing joelclaw bot identities
  (current Discord bot, Telegram bot) can be reused in place.
- **Gateway semantics mapping**: where do telegram-outbound-policy,
  error-emission-budget, message-journal, channel-health land — SDK
  equivalents, wrappers we keep, or losses to flag.
- **Stability**: release cadence vs breaking changes, versioning
  policy, issue tracker health — is "stabilize on this" true.
